<section id="Day1">
<a href="#Day1"><h2>Day1:Goa (Arrival) </h2></a>
<p>Upon your arrival at the Goa airport, get in touch with our representative who will assist you with a smooth transfer to the beach resort. Take rest for a while and then get ready for the outing. Your honeymoon trip to Goa starts with a boat cruise on the Mandovi River in the evening. Experience the thrill and luxury of traveling on-board with your spouse. While cruising in the river you will enjoy the DJ sessions, and Goan folk dances with a backdrop of clear blue sea and setting sun.
This is followed by your return to the hotel for dinner and an overnight stay.
</p>
</section>
<section id="Day2">
<a href="#Day2"><h2>Day2:North Goa</h2></a>
<p>On the 2nd day of your Goa honeymoon package, you will go on an excursion to North Goa. Enjoy your breakfast and then head towards North Goa. There are a few beaches in North Goa which are very popular among tourists including Baga Beach, Dona Paula, Calangute, and Miramar. You can stroll around these beaches and enjoy the special time with your significant other. You can also enjoy water sports activities like snorkeling, scuba diving, jet-skiing, and banana boat ride in Calangute. Other places where you can have a great time on Goa honeymoon are Fort Aguada and the ancient churches in Old Goa. The beautiful churches in Goa are a perfect amalgamation of Indian and Portuguese architecture.
Return to the resort in the evening and have a sumptuous dinner. Overnight stay at the hotel in Goa.
</p>
</section> 
<section id="Day3">
<a href="#Day3"><h2>Day3:South Goa</h2></a>
<p>Start the day with a delicious breakfast and make your way towards the beaches of South Goa. Some of the popular attractions of the Goa tour package for a couple includes the Santa Durga Temple, Colva Beach, and Mangeshi Temple, along with a few other places. Take a long walk on the golden sand of Colva Beach on a moony evening with the love of your life. Colva Beach is one of the famous tourist destinations among honeymooners. One can also enjoy the nightlife in Goa and relish the fascinating sightseeing of the dazzling places. One can also take part in water sports activities.
Return to the resort for dinner and overnight stay. 
</p>
</section> 
<section id="Day4">
<a href="#Day4"><h2>Day4:Goa</h2></a>
<p>After enjoying your breakfast in the morning, complete your check-out formalities at the hotel. With this, your Goa honeymoon package came to an end. Ride to the airport to board the flight</p>
